-- Hong Kong H-shares fall, pulled down by Chinese banks
-- By Grace Li
-- Tue May 27, 2014 04:06AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, May 27 (Reuters) - The index for Hong Kong listings of China companies on Tuesday had its biggest loss since May 9, pulled down by weaker Chinese bank stocks.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 0.1 percent at 22,944.30 points. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong was down 0.4 percent. Chinese banks were among the biggest index drags, with China Merchants Bank <3968.HK> down 1.7 percent and Industrial and Commercial Bank of China <1398.HK> off 0.2 percent.